00:16:15,171 --> 00:16:18,171
Not even holy enough, that's good.

275
00:16:19,171 --> 00:16:21,171
Miss Rottenmeier didn't want to have it.

276
00:16:21,171 --> 00:16:23,171
Forget it, Miss Rottenmeier.

277
00:16:27,693 --> 00:16:30,693
I think you like the cheese bread.

278
00:16:34,693 --> 00:16:36,693
Did something fall in there?

279
00:16:36,693 --> 00:16:38,693
Someone looked through the window.

280
00:16:38,693 --> 00:16:40,693
Through the window?

281
00:16:41,693 --> 00:16:45,693
You must have been mistaken. There was definitely no one there.

282
00:16:47,693 --> 00:16:49,693
Yes, there was someone again.

283
00:16:49,693 --> 00:16:51,693
Is there someone?

284
00:16:57,693 --> 00:17:03,693
What was that?

285
00:17:03,693 --> 00:17:05,693
I don't know.

286
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:10,693
Why are you driving around here in the middle of the night?

287
00:17:12,693 --> 00:17:14,693
Peter, can't you knock?

288
00:17:15,693 --> 00:17:16,693
Yes, I can.

289
00:17:19,693 --> 00:17:20,693
Just because...

290
00:17:22,693 --> 00:17:23,693
Because of what?

291
00:17:24,693 --> 00:17:25,693
Something important.

292
00:17:26,693 --> 00:17:28,693
That this is supposed to be for you.

293
00:17:28,693 --> 00:17:29,693
For me?

294
00:17:29,693 --> 00:17:31,693
I hope you like it. These are your favorite nuts.

295
00:17:31,693 --> 00:17:33,693
That's nice of you, Peter.

296
00:17:33,843 --> 00:17:35,843
I think so, too.

297
00:17:37,643 --> 00:17:40,843
You think so? Come on, General Siegen, come on in.

298
00:17:41,843 --> 00:17:44,843
Don't be like that. Come on in.

299
00:17:44,843 --> 00:17:47,843
You used to eat with us, too.

300
00:17:47,843 --> 00:17:51,843
Yes, but that was before.

301
00:17:51,843 --> 00:17:53,843
You weren't here anymore.

302
00:17:53,843 --> 00:17:55,843
Without you, I only dared to open the door.

303
00:17:55,843 --> 00:17:58,411
It was all so different all of a sudden.

304
00:17:58,411 --> 00:18:01,611
I didn't know if your grandfather still knew me, so do you know...

305
00:18:03,211 --> 00:18:04,811
Come here, you two, sit down.

306
00:18:05,011 --> 00:18:07,611
I don't understand a word of what you want to say.

307
00:18:07,811 --> 00:18:08,611
Later.

308
00:18:08,811 --> 00:18:10,811
Psst, I can't talk so well now.

309
00:18:11,011 --> 00:18:12,211
Is that why...

310
00:18:12,411 --> 00:18:15,411
After you were gone, he didn't talk to me anymore.

311
00:18:15,611 --> 00:18:18,611
When I brought the goats, he always looked at me in a bad way.

312
00:18:18,811 --> 00:18:20,011
Grandfather?

313
00:18:23,274 --> 00:18:27,274
That has to happen to me!

314
00:18:27,274 --> 00:18:30,274
Why don't you two sit down next to me?

315
00:18:30,274 --> 00:18:32,274
Where did you want to eat the world?

316
00:18:32,274 --> 00:18:36,274
And you, Peter, you're always hungry when I remember correctly.

317
00:18:36,274 --> 00:18:39,274
So what is it? I can't ask for more than that.

318
00:18:39,338 --> 00:18:40,538
He's changed.

319
00:18:40,538 --> 00:18:41,438
He's always like that.

320
00:18:41,438 --> 00:18:44,638
He hasn't changed at all. And you're a coward.

321
00:18:44,638 --> 00:18:46,338
Could be. Yes, maybe.

322
00:18:46,338 --> 00:18:48,338
Do you think he'll stay so friendly with me?

323
00:18:48,338 --> 00:18:51,338
Mhm. But only if you finally sit down.

324
00:18:51,838 --> 00:18:53,338
You go first.

325
00:18:54,138 --> 00:18:55,338
The pipe!

326
00:18:58,838 --> 00:19:00,038
Where is it?

327
00:19:00,038 --> 00:19:01,338
Well...

328
00:19:01,338 --> 00:19:03,838
There, Peter. I brought it with me.

329
00:19:05,538 --> 00:19:07,338
No, I can't accept that.

330
00:19:07,338 --> 00:19:08,826
Why?

331
00:19:08,826 --> 00:19:12,826
Actually, I wanted to give you a pipe, but you must have lost it somewhere.
Heidi, let go!

332
00:19:12,826 --> 00:19:17,826
You can accept that. Yes, for sure. Please accept it, please.

333
00:19:17,826 --> 00:19:21,826
You don't need that, Heidi. Thank you very much.

334
00:19:21,826 --> 00:19:27,826
Are you finally coming or not? I'm still here. Or have you forgotten that I'm
sitting here and waiting?

335
00:19:27,826 --> 00:19:30,826
I just want to say something. I'll pick you up tomorrow, okay?

336
00:19:30,826 --> 00:19:32,282
Peter!

337
00:19:32,282 --> 00:19:36,782
Well, tell me, do you want to go without eating? You're not sick, are you?

338
00:19:36,782 --> 00:19:39,782
No, but you used to stay here all the time.

339
00:19:39,782 --> 00:19:43,282
I promised your grandmother to come home soon.

340
00:19:43,282 --> 00:19:45,282
Aha.

341
00:19:46,282 --> 00:19:50,282
Even if there's cheese and fresh bread and dried meat?

342
00:19:50,282 --> 00:19:52,282
Meat?

343
00:19:54,282 --> 00:19:55,626
No, thank you very much.

344
00:19:55,626 --> 00:19:58,126
It looks good, but I should still go home.

345
00:19:58,126 --> 00:20:00,126
Why don't you take anything with you? Put it in the basket.

346
00:20:00,126 --> 00:20:02,126
That doesn't work.

347
00:20:04,126 --> 00:20:05,126
Why not?

348
00:20:17,126 --> 00:20:18,116
There!

349
00:20:18,116 --> 00:20:22,116
There was a star, Schnuppe. Now I can wish for something.

350
00:20:27,116 --> 00:20:28,116
What did you wish for?

351
00:20:28,388 --> 00:20:29,888
I'm not going to tell you.

352
00:20:29,888 --> 00:20:31,388
I can understand.

353
00:20:31,388 --> 00:20:33,388
Will you really stay here?

354
00:20:33,388 --> 00:20:35,888
I'll never go on in my life.

355
00:20:35,888 --> 00:20:37,388
Say hello to your grandmother!

356
00:20:37,388 --> 00:20:38,388
I will!

357
00:20:38,388 --> 00:20:40,688
Goodbye Peter! See you tomorrow! Get me out of here!

358
00:20:40,688 --> 00:20:42,688
Up! Up your legs!

359
00:21:06,208 --> 00:21:08,208
See you tomorrow!

360
00:21:10,688 --> 00:21:13,688
